               <location>
                  <geo>14.189278 39.362222</geo>
                  <height unit="m">2370.0</height>
               </location>
               <note>
                  <date type="foundation" notBefore="1600" notAfter="1600">1600-1600</date>
                  <desc type="foundation">Possibly diring the time of <persName ref="PRS6229LebnaDe">King Lǝbnā Dǝngǝl</persName> (r. <date>1508-1540</date>), re-established late 17th or early 18th cent. 
                     <persName ref="PRS6951Mazgaba">Mazgaba Śǝllāse</persName>, the late 17th - early 18th-cent. head of Gunda Gunde, played a role in the establishement of the local monastic community.</desc>
                  <ab type="history">Gadam. Some 10 monks were residing in the monastery at the time of the visit. &#xD;
                     </ab>
                  <ab type="description">22 Mss. photographed: <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm001">GKM-001</ref> "The Spiritual Elder"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm002">GKM-002</ref> "Miracles of Mary"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm003">GKM-003</ref> "The Book of the Chants"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm004">GKM-004</ref> "Miracles of Mary"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm005">GKM-005</ref> "Four Gospels"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm006">GKM-006</ref> "The Rite of the Holy Week"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm007">GKM-007</ref> "Homily of the Living One"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm008">GKM-008</ref> "Pauline Epistles"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm009">GKM-009</ref> "Synaxarion (September)"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm010">GKM-010</ref> "The Book of the Funeral Rite"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm011">GKM-011</ref> "Synaxarion (March)"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm012">GKM-012</ref> "Miracles of Mikaʾel"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm013">GKM-013</ref> "Vita of Mäzgäbä Śǝllase"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm014">GKM-014</ref> "Psalter"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm015">GKM-015</ref> "Prayer of Incense"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm016">GKM-016</ref> "Miracles of Jesus"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm017">GKM-017</ref> "The Covenant of Mary"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm018">GKM-018</ref> "Psalter"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm019">GKM-019</ref> "Collection of Maryam Texts and hymns"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm020">GKM-020</ref> "Prayers of Mary"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm021">GKM-021</ref> "The Book of the Baptismal Rite; The Book of the Baptismal Rite"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESgkm022">GKM-022</ref> fragments of a Missal and a Psalter.</ab>
                  <ab type="tabot"> <measure quantity="44"/>   Tābots: said to be "44", i.e. very many, both wooden and marble; specifically were mentioned tābots of 
                     <persName ref="PRS10775Trinity" type="tabot">Trinity</persName>, <persName ref="PRS6951Mazgaba" type="tabot">Mazgaba Śǝllāse</persName>, 
                     <persName ref="PRS7049Michael" type="tabot">Michael</persName>, <persName ref="PRS5684JesusCh#MadhaneAlam" type="tabot">Madḫāne ʿĀlam</persName>, <persName ref="PRS6819Mary" type="tabot">Mary</persName>.  
                     Possibly there exists also specifically <persName ref="PRS10776Kidan" type="tabot">Kidāna Mǝḥrat</persName>.
</ab>               </note>
